		<body>
			<div type="transcription">
				<div type="original" xml:lang="cs">
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-017_01.png" n="1"/>
					<p>Protokol č. 59</p>
					<p>Zpráva o <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">koncentračním</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">táboře</term>
						<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp">Mauthausen</placeName></p>
					<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2892267/katzdorf.html">Katzdorf</placeName>, <date when="1945-10-21">21. X. 1945</date></p>
					<p>Za <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-657" type="subject">Dokumentační akci</term> přijal: <persName ref="#ehri_dc_shek_zeev">Scheck</persName></p>
					<p>Za archiv přijal: <persName ref="#ehri_dc_tressler_harald">Tressler</persName></p>
					<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Praha</placeName>, <date when="1946-01-29">29. I. 1946</date></p>
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-017_02.png" n="2"/>
					<p>V <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2892267/katzdorf.html">Katzdorfu</placeName> dne <date when="1945-10-21">21. 10. 1945</date></p>
					<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-657" type="subject">Dokumentační akce</term>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2892267/katzdorf.html">Katzdorf</placeName></p>
					<p>Zpráva o <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">konc</term>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">táboře</term>
						<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp">Mauthausenu</placeName></p>
					<p>Dne <date when="1945-10-21">21. října 1945</date> navštívili jsme bývalý <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">koncentrační</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">tábor</term>
						<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp">Mauthausen</placeName>.</p>
					<p><placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp">Mauthausenský</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">tábor</term> se skládá hlavně z <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">tábora</term>
						<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp">Mauthausen</placeName>, z <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">tábora</term>
						<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-585" type="camp">Gusen</placeName> a jiných. Byl střediskem, ze kterého se posílala <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-489" type="subject">aussenkommanda</term> do různých zbrojních
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929" type="subject">závodů</term>, např. do <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2771682/melk.html">Melku</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html">Vídně</placeName>,
							<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2772400/linz.html">Lince</placeName>, atd.</p>
					<p>Ve vlastním <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">táboře</term>
						<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp">Mauthausen</placeName> je <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">ubytována</term> t. č. <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">ruská</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">posádka</term>. Dokumenty a celý archiv byl odvezen <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">Američany</placeName>, zčásti prý také bývalým <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">polským</placeName> a <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">čsl.</placeName> komitétem.</p>
					<p>Prohlédli jsme za vedení <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">ruského</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1084" type="subject">velitele</term> stráže <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">tábor</term> a proslulý <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-944" type="subject">kamenolom</term>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">Tábor</term> sám není příliš velký, měl dle údajů kolem 10.000 osazenstva. Pod hlavním <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">táborem</term> byl t.zv. <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">ruský</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">tábor</term>, chatrné <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">baráky</term>, které byly většinou <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">Američany</placeName> spáleny, poněvadž byly úplně zaplaveny hmyzem. Tam byl umístěn též <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-491" type="subject">Krankenbau</term>.</p>
					<p>V <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">táboře</term> jsme viděli t. č. čisté <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">baráky</term>, <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">krematorium</term>, poměrně malé s třemi peci, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">bunkry</term>, sklepové <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">místnosti</term>, kde se konaly rychlé <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">popravy</term>, a <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">plynové</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">komory</term>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">Popravy</term> se tam konaly různým způsobem. Ve sklepě byli lidé <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">usmrceni</term> pomocí zvláštních pistolí, které měly místo nábojů 6 – 7 cm dlouhý hřebík na peru, který se vstřelil do lebky odsouzeného a zase vytáhl. Dále byly <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">plynové</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">komory</term>, kterých se použilo v době před <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">osvobozením</term> k <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">odpravení</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">nemocných</term> s kapacitou kolem 300 denně.</p>
					<p>Hlavním <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">popravištěm</term> však byl <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-944" type="subject">kamenolom</term>. Je to místo, kde ještě dnes návštěvník podléhá hrůze.
						Dívá-li se na toto místo, vidí před očima strašný obraz otrocké <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">práce</term> tisíců <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">vězňů</term>. Je jasné, že
						tuto <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">práci</term> nemohl vydržeti nikdo po delší dobu. Asi 80 m vysoká hladká skalní stěna. Po celé stěně se hemžili vysílení bosí ubožáci v <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">hadrech</term>. Chodili do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">práce</term> asi 1000 m z <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">tábora</term> po cestě dlážděné hrbolatými žulovými kameny ostře hranatými, a protože jejich <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-944" type="subject">pracoviště</term>
						bylo tak <q>blízko</q>, byly tomuto <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-489" type="subject">komandu</term> odebrány z úsporných důvodů <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">dřeváky</term>, aby nebyly
						ničeny. Bosí chodili do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">práce</term> a bosí taky nosili nejtěžší balvany ony strašné schody nahorů, kterých jsme napočítali 196. Schody jsou nepravidelné, šikmé, klouzavé. Při tom byli <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">vězňové</term> neustále popoháněni <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1438" type="subject">dozorci</term>, ba museli dokonce poklusem s nákladem do schodů. Upadl-li
						nějaký ten ubožák vysílením nebo nesl-li kámen, který se zdál <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">esesákovi</term> příliš malým, byla to hned Arbeitssabotage. Pro Arbeitssabotage byl jen jeden <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-653" type="subject">trest</term>, a to svržení ze skály do smrtelné hloubky. Tím způsobem <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">skonalo</term> denně 100 až 200 lidí.
						Zakrvácená roztříštěná <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">těla</term> museli pak kamarádi odvléci do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">krematoria</term>.</p>
					<p>V posledním roce nebyly dělány rozdíly mezi židovskými a ostatními <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">vězni</term>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">Stravování</term> bylo totéž
						jako v jiných <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">koncentračních</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">táborech</term>.</p>
					<p>V <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-491" type="subject">Krankenbau</term> bylo kolem <date when="1945-04-15">15. dubna 1945</date> asi 8000 pacientů, většina <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject"
							>infekční</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">choroby</term>, zejména <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-493" type="subject">tyfus</term> a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292"
							type="subject">tuberkulosa</term>. Tehdy vyšel onen <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000181">Himmlerův</persName> rozkaz o zničení osazenstva <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject"
							>koncentračních</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">táborů</term> a začalo se se <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-534" type="subject">zaplynováním</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">nemocných</term>. Asi 3000 osob bylo <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-534" type="subject">zaplynováno</term> a spáleno během 10 dnů.</p>
					<p><date when="1945-05-08">8. května 1945</date> byl <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">tábor</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">osvobozen</term>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">Američany</placeName>. Stav <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">nemocných</term> byl takový, že ještě po <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">osvobození</term> zemřelo přes 1000 osob. Vkusně a důstojně upravený <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-747" type="subject">hřbitov</term> těchto poválečných <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-132" type="subject">obětí</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-381" type="subject">nacismu</term>,</p>
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-017_03.png" n="3"/>
					<p>je umístěn na bývalém <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">esesáckém</term> hřišti. Dlouhé řady malých bílých dřevěných křížů jsou popsány jmény a zkratkou <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1147"
							type="subject">národnosti</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">zemřelých</term>, ovšem že na mnohých stojí <q>unknown</q>, a to v případech, kde <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">osvoboditelé</term> našli již
						jen <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">mrtvá</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">těla</term>, jichž tam byly celé hromady, a jež nebylo možno identifikovati. Řady křížů jsou přerušeny <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-338" type="subject"
							>žlutými</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-338" type="subject">hvězdami</term> upevněnými na tyčce: tak jsou <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-338" type="subject">označeny</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-748" type="subject">hroby</term> židovských <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">vězňů</term>. Našli jsme však na celé řadě křížů jména, která nás nenechala v nejistotě
						o tom, že se jedná o židy /Kantorowicz, Spitz Schwarz, Weisz, Pollak/. Podobný <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-747" type="subject">hřbitov</term> se nachází u <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject"
							>koncentračního</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">tábora</term>
						<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-585" type="camp">Gusen</placeName> u <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2766701/sankt-georgen-an-der-gusen.html">St. Georgen</placeName>, jehož <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">baráky</term> jsou skoro všechny spáleny a zničeny.</p>
					<p>Koncem <date when="1945-07">července</date> převzali <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">Rusové</placeName> celý kraj do své správy. Nařídili vyklizení <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp"
							>Mauthausenu</placeName>. Asi 330 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">nemocných</term> bylo převezeno do <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2892267/katzdorf.html">Katzdorfu</placeName>, asi 18 km od <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp">Mauthausenu</placeName> vzdáleném. Byli to většinou židé <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">polského</placeName>, <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">maďarského</placeName> a <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3077311/czechia.html">československého</placeName> původu. T. č. se nachází v <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2892267/katzdorf.html"
							>Katzdorfu</placeName> ještě 42 pacientů. <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Českoslovenští</placeName> státní příslušníci a příslušníci <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/687869/zakarpattia-oblast.html">Zakarpatské</placeName>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/687869/zakarpattia-oblast.html">Ukrajiny</placeName> jsou uvedeni na přiložené listině.</p>
					<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-282" type="subject">Nemocnice</term> v <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2892267/katzdorf.html">Katzdorfu</placeName> je vedena <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html"
							>polským</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject">lékařem</term> drem. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_cederbaum">Cederbaumem</persName>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">Stravování</term> je uspokojivé,
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-280" type="subject">léků</term> je dostatek, jsou však stížnosti na <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-329" type="subject">protižidovské</term> chování <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">rakouských</placeName> úřadů /okresního hejtmanství v <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2769105/perg.html">Pergu</placeName>/, kterému čelí jenom podporou <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">ruského</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1084" type="subject">velitele</term> v <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2769105/perg.html">Pergu</placeName>.</p>
					<p>Část informací o <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">koncentračním</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">táboře</term>
						<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp">Mauthausen</placeName> nám poskytl <persName ref="#ehri_dc_skorny_tadeusz">Tadeusz Skorny</persName> z <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3099434/gdansk.html">Gdaňska</placeName>.</p>
					<p>Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_nasch_erich">Nasch</persName></p>
					<p>Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_weinberger_robert">Weinberger</persName></p>
				</div>
				<div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-017_01.png" n="1"/>
					<p>Statement no. 59</p>
					<p>Report on the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp">Mauthausen</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term></p>
					<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2892267/katzdorf.html">Katzdorf</placeName>, <date when="1945-10-21">October 21st, 1945</date></p>
					<p>Accepted on behalf of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-657" type="subject">Documentation Campaign</term> by: <persName ref="#ehri_dc_shek_zeev">Scheck</persName></p>
					<p>Accepted on behalf of the archive: <persName ref="#ehri_dc_tressler_harald">Tressler</persName></p>
					<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName>, <date when="1946-01-29">January 29th, 1946</date></p>
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-017_02.png" n="2"/>
					<p>In <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2892267/katzdorf.html">Katzdorf</placeName> on <date when="1945-10-21">October 21st, 1945</date></p>
					<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-657" type="subject">Documentation Campaign</term>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2892267/katzdorf.html">Katzdorf</placeName></p>
					<p>Report on the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp">Mauthausen</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">Concentration</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">Camp</term></p>
					<p>On <date when="1945-10-21">October 21st, 1945</date>, we visited the former <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp">Mauthausen</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term>.</p>
					<p>The <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp">Mauthausen</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term> consists mostly of the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp">Mauthausen</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term>, the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-585" type="camp">Gusen</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term>, and others. It was a center from which the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-489" type="subject">aussenkommando</term> sent prisoners to work in various
						munitions <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929" type="subject">plants</term>, for example to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2771682/melk.html">Melk</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html"
							>Vienna</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2772400/linz.html">Linz</placeName>, etc.</p>
					<p>A <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">Russian</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">company</term> is currently <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">staying</term> in the <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp">Mauthausen</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term> section. Documents and the entire archive were taken away by the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">Americans</placeName>, and parts thereof by the
						former <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Polish</placeName> and <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czechoslovak</placeName> committee.</p>
					<p>Under the leadership of the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">Russian</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1084" type="subject">commander</term>, we inspected the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term> guards and the infamous <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-944" type="subject">quarry</term>. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term> itself is not very large. According to the statistics, it had a population of
						around 10,000. Under the main <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term>, there was a so-called <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">Russian</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term>, ramshackle <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barracks</term> that were mostly burned down by the <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">Americans</placeName> because they were completely infested with insects. This is also where the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-491" type="subject">hospital</term> was located.</p>
					<p>In the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term>, we saw cleaned out <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barracks</term>, the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">crematorium</term>, which was relatively small and had three ovens, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">bunkers</term>, the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">rooms</term> in the cellar where quick <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">executions</term> took place, and the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">gas</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">chambers</term>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">Executions</term> were carried out in various ways. In the cellar, people were <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killed</term> with a special pistol that, instead of regular bullets, shot a 6-7 cm long nail into the head of the condemned that was subsequently removed to be used again. The <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">gas</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">chambers</term> that were utilized in order to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">do away with</term> the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick</term> before the camp’s <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">liberation</term> had a capacity of around 300 per day.</p>
					<p>However, the main <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">place of execution</term> was the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-944" type="subject">quarry</term>. It’s a place that horrifies even today’s
						visitors. If you look at it, you’ll see the image of the terrible slave <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">labor</term> of thousands of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject"
							>prisoners</term> with your very own eyes. It’s obvious that nobody could have endured this hard <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> for very long. Its smooth wall was about 80 metres high and teemed with
						exhausted, barefoot wretches dressed only in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">rags</term>. The prisoners walked the roughly 1,000 m to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject"
							>work</term> from the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term> on a road paved with sharp granite stones, and because their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-944" type="subject"
							>workplace</term> was so <q>close,</q> for cost-saving reasons this <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-489" type="subject">commando</term>’s <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">clogs</term> were
						taken away in order to preserve them from being damaged. They walked to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> barefoot and carried the heaviest boulders up the awful steps (we counted 196 in total) also barefoot. The
						steps were uneven, crooked, slippery. All the while, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">prisoners</term> were constantly and violently prodded by the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1438"
							type="subject">guards</term>. They even had to jog up the stairs while carrying their heavy loads. If any of them fell over from exhaustion or couldn’t carry a stone that an <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-man</term>
						deemed too small, it was immediately considered Arbeitssabotage. There was only one <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-653" type="subject">punishment</term> for Arbeitssabotage — being thrown from a deathly height. Every day, 100 to 200 people <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">perished</term> in this cruel way. Later, their friends had to take their bloody and shattered <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">bodies</term> back
						to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">crematorium</term>.</p>
					<p>In the camp’s last year, no differences were made between Jewish and other <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">prisoners</term>. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> was
						the same as in other <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camps</term>.</p>
					<p>Around <date when="1945-04-15">April 15th, 1945</date>, there were roughly 8,000 patients in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-491" type="subject">hospital</term>, most of them suffering from <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">infectious</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">diseases</term>, especially <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-493" type="subject">typhus</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292"
							type="subject">tuberculosis</term>. Then, <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000181">Himmler</persName> issued the order to destroy the remaining occupants of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496"
							type="subject">concentration</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camps</term> and so the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick</term> began to be <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-534" type="subject">gassed</term>. About 3,000 people were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-534" type="subject">gassed</term> and burned in 10 days.</p>
					<p>On <date when="1945-05-08">May 8th, 1945</date>, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term> was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">liberated</term> by the <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">Americans</placeName>. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick</term> were in such a poor state of health that over 1,000 of them died after they were <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">liberated</term>. A tastefully and reverently maintained <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-747" type="subject">cemetery</term> for the post-war <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-132" type="subject">victims</term> of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-381" type="subject">Nazi regime</term></p>
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-017_03.png" n="3"/>
					<p>is located on the site of the former <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term> sports grounds. Long rows of small, white wooden crosses are marked with the names and abbreviations of the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1147" type="subject">nationalities</term> of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">deceased</term>, but many have the word <q>unknown</q> written on them. In these
						graves lie the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">dead</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">bodies</term> that the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">liberators</term> found but couldn’t identify. There were whole piles of them there. Many
						rows of crosses have <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-338" type="subject">yellow</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-338" type="subject">stars</term> attached to them, which is how the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-748" type="subject">graves</term> of Jewish <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">prisoners</term> are <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-338" type="subject">marked</term>. We found many other names that we thought might be Jewish (Kantorowicz, Spitz
						Schwarz, Weisz, Pollak). A similar <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-747" type="subject">cemetery</term> is located by the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-585" type="camp">Gusen</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term> near <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2766701/sankt-georgen-an-der-gusen.html">St. Georgen</placeName>. Almost all of the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barracks</term> of this camp have been burned down and destroyed.</p>
					<p>At the end of <date when="1945-07">July</date>, the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">Russians</placeName> assumed control over the entire region. They ordered the liquidation of <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp">Mauthausen</placeName>. About 330 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick people</term> were transferred to <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2892267/katzdorf.html">Katzdorf</placeName>, roughly 18 km away from <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp">Mauthausen</placeName>. Most were <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Polish</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">Hungarian</placeName>, and <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3077311/czechia.html">Czechoslovak</placeName> Jews. There are
						currently still 42 patients in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2892267/katzdorf.html">Katzdorf</placeName>. <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czechoslovak</placeName> citizens and citizens of <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/687869/zakarpattia-oblast.html">Carpathian</placeName>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/687869/zakarpattia-oblast.html">Ukraine</placeName> are listed on the attached document.</p>
					<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-282" type="subject">hospital</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2892267/katzdorf.html">Katzdorf</placeName> is led by a <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html"
							>Polish</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject">doctor</term>, Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_cederbaum">Cederbaum</persName>. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> is satisfactory and
						there is enough <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-280" type="subject">medicine</term>, but there are complaints about the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-329" type="subject">anti-Jewish</term> behavior of the
							<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Austrian</placeName> authorities (regional authority in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2769105/perg.html">Perg</placeName>), who are only supported by the <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">Russian</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1084" type="subject">commander</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2769105/perg.html">Perg</placeName>.</p>
					<p>Some of the information about the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp">Mauthausen</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term> was provided by <persName ref="#ehri_dc_skorny_tadeusz">Tadeusz Skorny</persName> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3099434/gdansk.html">Gdańsk</placeName>.</p>
					<p>Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_nasch_erich">Nasch</persName></p>
					<p>Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_weinberger_robert">Weinberger</persName></p>
				</div>
			</div>
